text: Sungai Durian, or "Durian River", also called Sei Durian is a village in the district of Banua Lawas, Tabalong Regency in the province of South Kalimantan, Indonesia. The village had 837 inhabitants as of the 2010 census. ==Notes== ==Sources== * * Category:Populated places in South Kalimantan
title: Sungai Durian, Tabalong
